## Plan Summary

Here's what I found and what the plan calls for — **only `common/chat.cpp` needs to change**, no modifications to `chat.h`.

---

### What I explored

- `common/chat.h`: `COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY` already exists in the enum (value 0). No changes needed.
- `common/chat.cpp`: Six existing specialized handlers all follow the same signature pattern. The dispatch function `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` (line 1634) pattern-matches the Jinja source string and returns `std::nullopt` if nothing matches.
- **Key distinction**: The existing Ministral 3 handler fires when `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` **is present**. The new handler fires when `[INST]`/`[/INST]` are present but `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` is **absent** — mutually exclusive, no collision risk.

---

### Two edits to `common/chat.cpp`

**Edit 1** — Insert new handler function (~line 1518, after `gigachat_v3` closes):

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;
    std::string prompt;
    std::string system_content;
    bool        first_user = true;

    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        const auto role    = msg.value("role", "");
        const auto content = msg.value("content", "");
        if (role == "system") {
            system_content = content;
        } else if (role == "user") {
            if (first_user) {
                prompt += tmpl.bos_token() + "[INST] ";
                if (!system_content.empty()) prompt += system_content + "\n";
                prompt += content + " [/INST]";
                first_user = false;
            } else {
                prompt += "[INST] " + content + " [/INST]";
            }
        } else if (role == "assistant") {
            prompt += " " + content + "</s>";
        }
    }
    data.prompt = prompt;
    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY;
    return data;
}
```

**Edit 2** — Insert detection block before `return std::nullopt;` (~line 1690):

```cpp
if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos && src.find("[/INST]") != std::string::npos &&
    src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
    LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v3\n");
    return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
}
```

